      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''New Climate Thriller: Scary, but Is It Science?'' (Dec. 14): According to Michael Crichton's latest novel, warnings about the growing dangers posed by global warming are false alarms sounded by environmental extremists.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''New Climate Thriller: Scary, but Is It Science?'' (Dec. 14): According to Michael Crichton's latest novel, warnings about the growing dangers posed by global warming are false alarms sounded by environmental extremists.</p>
        <p>On the contrary, it is actually the mainstream view of climatologists and scientists in relevant disciplines that global warming is real and, if unchecked, could result in ecological disasters.</p>
        <p>Personally, I don't believe it is very difficult to decide whose views are more credible.</p>
        <p>RUSS WEISS  Princeton, N.J.</p>
      </block>
